        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-07-04 08:16:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(6 comments)\n\nIn addition to the comments below, I think it would be better to validate the URL in the validate() method of the RestClientCarriertechnologyParameters and the RestRequestorCarriertechnologyParameters class.\n\nIn this class, we can validate that there are no hanging '{' or '}' braces and no nesting etc. Then in the execution we don't have to worry about those cases.\n\nThis review reminds me that there is a lot of duplication in the code in these plugins. Let's look at that in Frankfurt. I just created POLICY-1884 for that.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
